http://news.ycombinator.com/item?id=3654750

1. Install dotjs addon for Firefox: https://github.com/rlr/dotjs-addon
2. Copy dotjs/default.js to ~/.js/
3. npm install
4. ./run_server
5. plugins/email.coffee - fill in the blanks if you want to send emails 
6. in the browser on the top right corner you should see a yellow square
7. press F1 to activate the console (pig.js line 24 to change the key) 
8. input #tag #tag2 to save tags, !tag !tag2 to remove them
9. input @cosmin to send me an email with the link of your the current browser page
